* `$tw.utils.pulseElement()` listens for the standard `animationend` event instead of the removed `$tw.browser.animationEnd`, so the pulse animation runs and cleans up its CSS class again, and the vanilla theme defines the missing `pulse` animation (fixes [[Issue #6835|https://github.com/TiddlyWiki/TiddlyWiki5/issues/6835]])
